me.elrod.pureio

Class PureConsoleIOT<A>

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.elrod.pureio.PureConsoleIOT<A>

  • public abstract class PureConsoleIOT<A>
extends java.lang.Object
    A trampolining free IO monad over TerminalOperation. PureConsoleIOT takes the same approach to trampolining as Trampoline except it is specialized to TerminalOperation because Java doesn't give us the ability to abstract over type constructors. So, much of this is like a huge copypaste mix of PureConsoleIO and Trampoline into one mess of a structure. The end result, however, is a trampolining free IO monad. Where Trampoline is Codensity (Free Identity), and PureConsoleIO is Free TerminalOperation, PureConsoleIOT is Codensity (Free TerminalOperation). We include a run method which can be passed an interpreter. The interpreter should use TerminalOperation.cata(java.util.function.BiFunction<java.lang.String, A, B>, java.util.function.Function<java.util.function.Function<java.lang.String, A>, B>, java.util.function.BiFunction<java.lang.Integer, A, B>).
